        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 9:13AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 912 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Jim Hogg County Airport, or near Hebbronville, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Realitos and Bruni.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
